 we began to suffer, we had to get away from there because our physical strength did not permit us to remain at such hard labor."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "867.039","u": "Did you have with you the [volumes of] Talmud, did you have [with you] any books?"},    {"who": "Isaac Ostland", "start": "869.991","u": "No, no books. We only studied&#226;we had with us a little Tanakh-Pentateuch, Prophets and Writings. And there were some among us who knew [the scripture] by heart, so we held every Saturday conferences reciting the words of the Bible or the scriptures which we knew by heart."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "883.873","u": "So."},    {"who": "Isaac Ostland", "start": "884.788","u": "And every day we had a [set] time for study, and we prayed three times a day."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "888.814","u": "The Russians permitted it?"},    {"who": "Isaac Ostland", "start": "890.355","u": "The Russians were not with us at all. We managed to find definite time that would not interfere with the work."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "896.424","u": "But you worked for the Russians?"},    {"who": "Isaac Ostland", "start": "898.208","u": "We worked for the Russians, for the authorities."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "900.090","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Isaac Ostland", "start": "900.384","u": "We were able to observe the Sabbath because we worked on Sunday."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "903.219","u": "So they demonstrated religious tolerance?"},    {"who": "Isaac Ostland", "start": "908.504","u": "They did not bother us and also permitted us to choose our own day of rest."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "912.280","u": "So . . . well, but you worked for the government, did you get any pay?"},    {"who": "Isaac Ostland", "start": "917.938","u": "The pay consisted of our food which we were given, our working clothes and the lodging and the tools for work which we needed . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "927.967","